
{center}
{subhead} Strange Opinion{def}{p}
Article by Mark Tierno
{left}
{p} {p}

Well, it's Dr. Strange here again, with another strange opnion. THis
time it's meant for any execs at Gateway and Amiga seeking advice for
rapid advancement.
{p} {p}
As the courts have just announced, Microsoft has been officiall declared
a Monopoly (like we all didn't know), and might be only a couple of
steps away from breakup by the government. This is an unparalleled
opportunity for one to strike. You know Apple is going to leverage
itself into the market with it's G3/G4 line and use this stumbling block
to their arch-enemy to back some much needed ground, so why can't the
Amiga?
{p} {p}
Finish off some product boys, get some hardware and software going, or
just commission it and give it that legal stamp of approval that your
advertising department needs then PUSH that puppy for all it's worth.
Gates is on the ropes, the PC world is about to fissure. There is NO
better time to break into the shark-infested gome-computer waters and
do some serious damage.
{p} {p}
Let's follow Apple's example and help them drive that stake through the
Wintel heart. There won't be another opportunity.